intro.content: Hi and welcome to Food Farmer!
We're all here to pitch in.  I like to dig holes to grow our plants.
She's got a whole bunch of them to choose from.
Mindy is going to plant our plants.  We are going to start with carrots.

level1ActionSelect.content: Tap on the "shovel button" and I will dig there.
Tap anywhere else if you don't want to dig.

level1Begin.content: It's time to grow our garden.
We have two gardeners.  I dig, and Mindy plants seeds.
Tap anywhere on the ground to start.

level1HoleDug.content: We dug a hole!  Now tap on it,
and select a carrot seed to plant there.

level1Pan.content: Tap and drag to the left, or right to see more of your garden.

levelSelectFirstVisit.content: First, we'll grow a garden on Earth,
but later on we'll go to Mars and Mercury.

mag-hole.content: When you reach a certain score, shown here, you will unlock

magAphid.content: Tap to remove them from the garden
before they suck the juice from our plants.

magBee.content: They help move pollen from one flower to another,
and that helps fruit grow on your plants!

magButterfly.content: They help move pollen from one plant to another.

magCloud.content: This blocks the sun from shining brightly on our plants.

magCompost.content: Plants that didn't grow very well go here
After awhile, it will turn into something that is super-healthy for the soil.

magHarvest.content: This shows you what plants you can grow, and also
how many you have grown and harvested.

magHole.content: A hole! We should plant a seed in it soon.

magJet.content: I use my shovel to dig holes and harvest plants.

magMindy.content: She plants all the different types of seeds.

magPotato.content: A potato! Who doesn't like mashed potatoes?

magPumpkin.content: A pumpkin! Oh, good for pumpkin pie!

magRadish.content: A radish: these are great in salads.

magRock.content: A rock: this will block you from digging or planting.
Tap to remove it from your garden.

magSean.content: He waters the plants to help them grow.

magSeed-1.content: A seed: with enough water and sun,
it will sprout and start to grow into a plant.

magSeed-2.content: This tells us what each plant needs to grow its very best.

magSeed.content: A seed. With enough water and sun,
it will sprout and start to grow into a plant.

magSydney.content: She puts compost in the soil around the plants to keep them healthy.

magTomato.content: Tomatoes: great for spaghetti sauce and on salads.

magWeed.content: This will block you from digging or planting.
So, have me dig it up soon.

mars.content: Sunlight on Mars is much weaker than sunlight on Earth,
because Mars is farther away from the Sun.
Growing will be a little different.  Good luck!

mercury.content: Since it's so close to the Sun,
sunlight is over 6 times stronger than sunlight on Earth.
We'll have to find some way to block it when it gets too sunny.

mercurySun.content: Tap those Sun icons before they touch the ground,
or else your plants will be damaged.

milestones1.content: You scored a lot of points and earned some potato and pumpkin seeds!

milestones2.content: You've unlocked a new type of gardener.

milestones4.content: You just unlocked the greenhouse on Mars.  Awesome!
When you are ready, use the "home button" to return
to the level select screen and start farming there.

milestones5.content: You just unlocked lettuce.  Nice work!

milestones6.content: You just unlocked tomatoes.  Good job!

milestones7.content: You just unlocked the greenhouse on Mercury.  Awesome!
When you are ready, use the "home button" to return
to the level select screen and start farming there.

needSpace.content: You'll have to dig it up, or dig up the other plants around it.

plantBad.content: Uh oh.  This plant isn't healthy.
We can't use it for food,
but we can use it to make compost for the soil.
Tap on it, and then the button showing the compost bin and shovel.

plantGood1.content: You watered your plant and gave it enough space to grow.
It's healthy and ready to be picked.
Tap the plant.  Then, tap the button with the basket and shovel.

plantGood1_alt.content: Then, tap the button with the basket and shovel.

plantGood2.content: Your plant is in your basket.
Each time you pick healthy plants, you get points.
The healthier your plant is, the more points you get.

plantGood_ALT 1.content: Your plant is in your basket.
Each time you pick healthy plants you get points.
The healthier your plant is, the more points you get.

plantGood_ALT 2.content: Your plant is in your basket.
Each time you pick healthy plants, you get points.
The healthier your plant is, the more points you get.

plantPick1.content: Great job!  Your plant is fully grown and ready to be picked.
Tap on the plant and choose the "shovel button" to collect your plant.

plantPick2.content: Good work!  Your plant is fully grown and ready to get picked.
Click on it.  When you see the shovel, tap on the shovel to collect your plant.

title.content: Welcome to the Food Farmer Game.
This is going to be so amazing.
Come help me and Mindy grow our own garden.
We're going to use the shrink ray to make us super
small, so we can see our vegetables up close.

tutorialAphid.content: They will climb up your plants and suck their juices.
Tap on them to remove them from the garden.

tutorialBee.content: Bees give flowers a health boost.
Tap on a bee to fly to a flower and give it a boost.

tutorialCompost.content: Sydney can add compost to the soil to make it healthy.
This will give your plant a big health boost.
She can only add compost once for each plant.

tutorialCompost2.content: You need to compost plants to add to your compost pile.
Weeds work well for this, and sometimes, old, dried up vegetables.

tutorialOverwater.content: Whoops!  You gave it too much water.
Wait for the soil to dry up before watering again.

tutorialQ.content: Your gardeners work hard and remember instructions
when you give them lots of things to do.
If you want to stop them from doing something, use the "cancel buttons" here.

tutorialRocks.content: This garden has rocky soil that makes it hard to dig holes for seeds.
Tap the rocks to get rid of them.

tutorialSeedInfo2.content: This package shows how much water, sun, and space your plant needs.
Look at the meter next to the water drop.
If the meter shows a little bit of blue,
your plant only needs a little bit of water.
If it shows a lot of blue, your plant needs a lot of water.

tutorialSeedInfo3.content: This meter shows how much sun your plant needs.
Does it need a lot, or a little?

tutorialSeedInfo4.content: This meter shows how much space your plant needs.
Does it need a lot or a little?
Here's a hint:  Plants that are bigger, like pumpkins,
often need more space to grow.

tutorialSeedInfo5.content: Tap on the left and right arrows to see information about the other seeds.

tutorialSeedPlanted1.content: This meter shows how much time it will take until your seed sprouts leaves.

tutorialSeedPlanted2.content: The rain will water your seed.

tutorialSprout.content: Your seed has sprouted!  It has leaves and shoots.
Check if it needs water, sun, or more space.
If you plant things too close together, they won't have room to keep growing.

tutorialSun-alt.content: Tap on the clouds, so bright sunlight can reach the plants.

tutorialSun.content: These floating clouds are blocking the Sun.
Tap to remove them, and get your plant more sunlight.

tutorialWaterSeed.content: Sean's here!  He can water the plants.
You don't just have to wait for it to rain.
After you plant a seed, tap the "water button" to water that seed.

tutorialWaterSeed2.content: Watering will give a plant all it needs for now,
but it might need water again later when the Sun dries up the water.

tutorialSeedInfo.content: Here you can choose other seeds to plant.
You can also tap on the seed packet button
to get information about each kind of seed.

weeds.content: This area is covered with weeds.
Tap on them, and then tap on the shovel and compost button
The weeds will be dug up and sent to the compost bin.

components.text:
A description of
 sorts, you know!

tutorial-seed-select-1.message: The hole is dug! Now select your seed gardener and click on the hole to plant a carrot seed.

tutorial-seed-select-2.message: Click a plant image in the seed select box to get information about how much water, sun and spacing it needs.

tutorial-seed-select-2-ALT.message: Click a plant icon in the seed select box to equip that seed.

tutorial-seed-select-4.message: Now that you have your seed, click a hole to put it in.

tutorial-seed-planted-1.message: Great, your seed is planted! This meter will show how long until it sprouts. Water and sun make the meter go up.

tutorial-seed-planted-2.message: For now, the rain will water your seed. Later on you will also water it with a new type of gardener.

tutorial-sun.message: Click the floating sun rays to give your plants sun!

tutorial-water-seed.message: You now have a gardener with a watering pail. Activate them and then click on seeds or plants to water.

tutorial-rocks.message: This garden has rocky soil, which will prevent you from digging holes.  Use your digging gardener to get rid of them!

tutorial-water-seed-2.message: Watering a plant will give it all the water it needs for now, but it might need it again later on.

tutorial-overwater.message: You gave it too much water!  Wait for the soil to dry up before watering again.

tutorial-sprout.message: Your seed has sprouted!  It will tell you if it needs water, sun or more space.  Space is important! If you plant things too close together, they will not grow very well.

weeds.message: This area is overgrown with weeds!  Use your digger to send them to the compost.

tutorial-compost.message: We also have a new character - the composter!  When it's time, activate that new gardener and then collect compost from the bin each time you need to apply some to a plant, which gives it a big health boost.

tutorial-compost-2.message: You need to compost plants to add to your compost pile. Weeds work well for this, and sometimes vegetables that didn't grow well.

plant-good-1.message: This plant is growing great and is ready to harvest!  Activate the garnder with the shovel and then click the plant.

plant-good-2.message: This plant has been added to your harvest basket! You also get a score for each harvested plant, depending on how big and healthy it was.

plant-bad.message: This plant isn't doing so well.  It could be it wasn't watered enough, or maybe didn't have enough space from other plants. Click the shovel to equip it, and then click the plant to dig it up and turn it into compost.

need-space.message: This plant needs more space... you will have to dig it up, or dig up other plants around it.
